node.accessibility_caption: Photo by GABBIE HANNA on September 10, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and indoor.

node.text:
the other day i went to home depot bc i convinced myself id fix the toilet in my art studio. while staring at a wall of items i clearly and most definitely had never seen before, a [very] cute guy in a hand-painted apron approached and asked if i needed help. i clearly and most definitely did. i asked him about his apron and he told me he’s a painter. me too, i said. we showed each other some of our stuff and said we should paint together sometime. 
-
i didn’t know you could paint acrylic onto clothing. never thought to even look it up. for a few weeks i’d been struggling with fabric paint which just didnt *hit the same.* i got super inspired and here we are.
-
my toilet is still broken. thanks for inspiring me, [very] cute home depot guy!
